HEADWORD: buffalo nickel
<hw>buffalo nickel</hw> <def>A United States five-cent coin minted from
1913 to 1937 having an image of an American bison
(⟦ldquo⟧buffalo⟦rdquo⟧) on its reverse, and an American Indian on the
obverse.</def>⟦br⟧
